functional_description:
1. Page Overview:
This is the landing page for a software product, likely a Python tool. The primary purpose is to introduce the product, highlight its features and benefits, and encourage users to get started or browse documentation.

2. Sections:
    *   Header: Contains the company logo, navigation links to Products, Docs, Blog, Company, and call-to-action to Get Started. Also contains a link to Github.
    *   Hero Section: Contains the heading "Next-Gen Python Tooling," subheadings "Get Started" and "Browse Docs", and introductory text about the company mission to make the Python ecosystem more productive.
    *   "Fast, unified, futuristic" section: Contains a description of the mission to make the Python ecosystem more productive with tools like Ruff.
    *   Ruff Section: Presents Ruff, an extremely fast Python linter. Includes the title "Lint at Lightspeed" and a description. Includes a button labeled "Learn More". Contains a table showing linting times for the CPython codebase using Ruff, AutoFlake, Flake8, PFlakes, PyCodeStyle, and Pylint, with corresponding time values (e.g., "0.00s").
    *   "Tried and tested" section: Contains the heading "Tried and tested. Powering impactful projects across open source." and includes testimonial quotes from users with their names and titles.
    *   "Open-source and permissively licensed" section: Contains text describing the open-source and permissively licensed nature of the product.
    *   "Space to think" section: Contains the heading "Space to think" and lists recent announcements with their titles and descriptions.
    *   Call to Action Section: Contains the heading "Supercharge your Python tooling" and calls-to-action to "Get Started" and "Browse Docs."
    *   Footer: Contains a list of links related to Ruff, Github, Company, Hiring, Blog, and a privacy policy link.

3. Interactive Elements:
    *   "Get Started" button in the header: Likely navigates to a signup or download page.
    *   "Browse Docs" button in the header: Likely navigates to the product documentation.
    *   "Learn More" button in the Ruff Section: Likely navigates to a page with more details about Ruff.
    *   "Get Started" and "Browse Docs" buttons in the Call to Action Section: Likely navigate to the same pages as the header buttons.
    *   Links to Ruff, UV, TY, PYX that probably link to related information.
    *   Links to Github, Company, Hiring, and Blog.

4. Content Details:
    *   Headings: "Next-Gen Python Tooling", "Fast, unified, futuristic", "Lint at Lightspeed", "Tried and tested. Powering impactful projects across open source.", "Space to think", "Supercharge your Python tooling"
    *   Navigation links: Products, Docs, Blog, Company
    *   Call-to-action texts: "Get Started", "Browse Docs", "Learn More"
    *   Testimonial quotes from users, including one from Sebastian Ramirez, Creator of FastAPI.
    *   Announcement titles: "ty: An extremely fast Python type checker and language server", "pyx: a Python-native package registry"
    *   Table data showing linting times for various tools.

1. Page Overview:
Landing page for Autumn, a service focusing on credits, limits, and usage billing, using AI to simplify pricing.

2. Sections:
*   Header: Contains links to "Github 2K", "Discord", "Blog", and "Docs". A link to "Dashboard" is also available.
*   Hero Section: Contains the heading "Credits, limits and usage billing. We make AI pricing easy.", a subheading describing the product as simplifying pricing plans and Stripe subscriptions. It also contains two buttons: "Start for free" and "Read docs". It shows that Autumn is backed by Y Combinator. Code snippets simulating an `autumn.config.ts` file are also visible, along with a popup displaying product feature information labeled "Pro" with associated usage.
*   Usage Examples: A section titled "How it works" describes the 3-step payments experience for developers. Steps include: "Handle any payment with one function", "Usage tracking, limits and billing", and "No webhooks required, just check for feature access". There are code snippets showing "Stripe without Autumn" and "Stripe with Autumn" along with "Expand code" interactive element.
*   Features: A section titled "Everything you'll need" with a subheading explaining Autumn is packed with features out of the box and allows pricing changes without touching code.
*   Testimonials: A section titled "Founders love Autumn" which displays testimonials from users.
*   Pricing Plans: A section titled "Start for Free" with a subheading describing Autumn's pricing structure. There are three pricing plans: "Builder", "Startup", and "Growth". The "Builder" plan is free until $8K monthly revenue and includes up to $8K processed monthly, support for 10 products and Discord support. The "Startup" plan is $375 per month, for $8K-$50K monthly revenue and includes up to $50K processed monthly, unlimited products and Slack support. The "Growth" plan is custom, for $50K+ MRR and includes over $50K MRR processed, unlimited products, and Slack support. There is a disclaimer regarding Stripe Billing fees.
*   Footer: Contains text "San Francisco & London" and a link to "Privacy Policy".

3. Interactive Elements:
*   "Start for free" button in the hero section, presumably starts a free trial.
*   "Read docs" button in the hero section, presumably navigates to documentation.
*   Code snippet labeled "Expand code".
*   "Start for free" button within the "Builder" pricing tier.
*   "Get started" button within the "Startup" pricing tier.
*   "Let's chat" button within the "Growth" pricing tier.
*   Links in the header to "Github 2K", "Discord", "Blog", "Docs", and "Dashboard".
*   Privacy Policy link in the footer.

4. Content Details:
*   Headings: "Credits, limits and usage billing. We make AI pricing easy.", "How it works", "Everything you'll need", "Founders love Autumn", "Start for Free".
*   Pricing tiers: "Builder", "Startup", "Growth".
*   Pricing details: "Free", "$375 per month", "Custom".
*   Feature lists within each pricing tier.
*   Testimonial quotes from users.
*   Code examples with labels such as "stripe.ts" and "upgrade-button.tsx".

1.  **Page Overview:**
    This is a landing page for a user management service. Its primary purpose is to showcase the features and benefits of the platform and encourage users to start building.

2.  **Sections:**
    *   **Header Section:** Contains the company logo "Clerk", links to "Products", "Docs", "Changelog", "Company", and "Pricing". It also has a notification of "Clerk raises $50m Series C". Contains a link to "Learn more". There are also links to "Sign in" and "Start building".
    *   **Hero Section:** Contains the heading "More than authentication, Complete User Management", a descriptive text "Need more than sign-in? Clerk gives you...", and a call-to-action button labeled "Start building for free." There is also a link to "Watch demo" with a duration of "2 min".
    *   **Logos Section:** Displays a set of company logos, with the text "Trusted by fast-growing companies around the world.". The logos are: Inngest, Durable, Upstash, Cartesia.
    *   **Clerk Components Section:** Headline: "Pixel-perfect UIs, embedded in minutes". Contains a description of the product and a link to "Explore all components". An interactive demonstration is shown that includes text fields for entering "First name", "Last name", "Email address", and a "Continue" button. A link says "Already have an account? Sign in". Also listed are User Authentication options.
    *   **Authentication Features Section:** Headline: "Everything you need for authentication". A subtitle is "Ever feel like the authentication requirements change with the seasons?". Includes sections for "Multi-factor Authentication", "Fraud and Abuse Prevention", "Session Management", "Social Sign-On", "Advanced Security", "Bot Detection", "Email and SMS one-time passcodes", "Magic Links", "Passwords". Each feature has a description.
    *   **Multi-tenancy Solution Section:** Headline: "The easy solution to multi-tenancy". Contains a description of the multi-tenancy feature and a link to "Explore B2B features". Includes sections for "Custom roles and permissions", "Organization UI Components", "Organization Management", "Invitations", "Enterprise Sign-on (SSO)".
    *   **Subscription Billing Section:** Headline: "Subscription billing, without the headache". Contains a description of the subscription billing feature and a list of benefits. A link to "Explore Billing features" is provided.
    *   **Tailor made pricing Section:** Headline: "Tailor made pricing from Acme, Inc.". There are two pricing tiers, each with different features and pricing. Each has a "Get Started" call to action.
    *   **Frameworks Section:** Headline: "Build with SDKs for modern frameworks". Contains a description of the modern frameworks feature and a link to "All frameworks".
    *   **Integrations Section:** Headline: "Integrate with the tools you love". Contains a description of the integrations feature and a link to "All Integrations".
    *   **Testimonials Section:** Headline: "Trusted by startups and the world's largest companies". Displays a set of quotes and testimonials from different companies.
    *   **Call to Action Section:** Headline: "Start now, no strings attached". Contains a description of the free plan and a call-to-action button labeled "Start building".
    *   **Footer Section:** Contains the company logo, links to "Product", "Developers", "Company", "Legal", and a copyright notice.

    *   The Hero Section contains a call-to-action button: "Start building for free".
    *   The Clerk Components section contains text fields for "First name", "Last name", "Email address", and a "Continue" button. It also contains a link for users who "Already have an account? Sign in".
    *   The Authentication Features section contains a link to "Explore user authentication".
    *   The Multi-tenancy Solution Section contains a link to "Explore B2B features".
    *   The Subscription Billing Section contains a link to "Explore Billing features".
    *   The Frameworks Section contains a link to "All frameworks".
    *   The Integrations Section contains a link to "All Integrations".
    *   Each pricing plan has a "Get started" call-to-action button.

        *   Heading: "Subscription billing, without the headache"
        *   Description: "Add subscriptions to your B2C or B2B application..."

        *   Heading: "Build with SDKs for modern frameworks"

1. Page Overview: Documentation page for a UI component called CheckoutButton, part of the Clerk SDK. The purpose is to explain the component and provide SDK-specific information.

2. Sections:
    *   Header: Contains the Clerk logo, a link to documentation, a search field for documentation, a button to ask AI, and a Sign Up button.
    *   Sidebar Navigation:
        *   Section to select the SDK. It contains the option "Expo."
        *   Section titled "Guides."
        *   Section titled "Reference," which expands to show "SDK Reference," "UI Components," and "API Reference."
        *   A list of components, which includes "Overview," "<ClerkProvider/>," "Authentication components," "User components," "Organization components," "Billing components" (expanded to show "<PricingTable />"), "Control components," and "Unstyled components."
    *   Main Content Area:
        *   Heading: "<CheckoutButton /> component".
        *   Description: "Clerk's <CheckoutButton /> component renders a button that opens the checkout drawer for Plan subscriptions."
        *   SDK Selection Section: "This page is available for the following SDKs. Select the SDK you would like to use:" Followed by sections for Next.js, React, and Vue.
    *   Cookie Consent Message: Contains a message regarding the use of cookies to improve the user experience, with links to the cookie policy and options to change preferences. It contains "Decline" and "Accept" buttons.
    *   Feedback Section: Asks "What did you think of this content?" and provides options for "It was helpful", "It was not helpful", and "I have feedback."
    *   Footer: Displays the last updated date (Jan 7, 2026), a link to "Edit on GitHub", the Clerk logo, a "Product" list with links to "Components", "Pricing", "Dashboard", "Feature requests" and "React authentication", a "Developers" list with links to "Documentation", "Discord server", "Support", "Glossary", and "Changelog", a "Company" list with links to "About", "Careers", "Blog", "Contact", and "Brand assets", a "Legal" list with links to "Terms and Conditions", "Terms of Engagement", "Privacy Policy", "Data Processing Agreement", "Do Not Sell/Share My Info", and "Cookie manager", and copyright information.

3. Interactive Elements:
    *   Search field: Allows searching the documentation.
    *   "Ask AI" button: Presumably opens a chat interface or performs an AI-powered search.
    *   "Sign Up" button: Navigates to a sign-up page.
    *   SDK Selector: Selects the SDK to view documentation for.
    *   Navigation links in the sidebar: Navigate to different sections of the documentation.
    *   Next.js, React, and Vue sections: Selecting one filters the documentation for the specific SDK.
    *   "Decline" button in cookie message: Declines the use of cookies.
    *   "Accept" button in cookie message: Accepts the use of cookies.
    *   "It was helpful" link: Registers positive feedback.
    *   "It was not helpful" link: Registers negative feedback.
    *   "I have feedback" link: Opens a feedback form.
    *   "Edit on GitHub" link: Navigates to the GitHub repository for this page.
    *   Links in the footer: Navigate to different pages.

4. Content Details:
    *   Page Title: "<CheckoutButton /> component"
    *   Component Description: "Clerk's <CheckoutButton /> component renders a button that opens the checkout drawer for Plan subscriptions."
    *   SDK selection instruction: "This page is available for the following SDKs. Select the SDK you would like to use:"
    *   SDK Options: "Next.js", "React", "Vue"
    *   Cookie Consent Text: "We use cookies to collect data to improve your experience on our site. Read our cookie policy. You can change your preferences at any time."
    *   Feedback Question: "What did you think of this content?"
    *   Feedback Options: "It was helpful", "It was not helpful", "I have feedback"
    *   Footer copyright notice: "© 2026 Clerk, Inc."

1. Page Overview:
This is the homepage of Fly.io, a platform for deploying applications. The primary purpose of the page is to introduce the platform and its features, and encourage users to start deploying their apps.

2. Sections:
  *   Header: Contains company logo, navigation links to Products, Docs, Customers, Pricing, Articles, Community, and Status, and buttons to Sign In or Get Started.
  *   Hero Section: Contains the headline "Build fast. Run any code fearlessly.", a descriptive paragraph about the platform, and a call-to-action button "Deploy your app".
  *   Feature Section 1: Contains a section titled "Modern Compute Without the Complexity" with a paragraph describing the compute capabilities of Fly Machines.
  *   Feature Section 2: Contains a section titled "Sandboxes That Feel Like a Superpower" with a paragraph describing hardware-isolated sandboxes, and a call-to-action button "Check 'em out!".
  *   Feature Section 3: Contains a section titled "Storage That Keeps Up" with a paragraph describing local NVMe and global object storage.
  *   Feature Section 4: Contains a section titled "Built-In Private Networking" with a paragraph describing private networks and encryption.
  *   Feature Section 5: Contains a list of features including "VMs That Do Everything You Need", "Fork Off VMs Like They're Processes", "Built for Distributed Systems", and "Get Right in Your Users' Faces", each with a short description.
  *   Tech Section: Contains a section titled "Use the Tech You Love" with a description of container generation capabilities and a list of frameworks (Rails, Phoenix, Django, Node, Laravel, and .NET), a "Learn More" link, and a "Next" button.
  *   Agents Section: Contains a section titled "Agents Run Better on Sprites" with a description of agents with CPU memory, networking, and a private filesystem and a call-to-action button "Build for scale from Day One".
  *   Trusted By Section: Contains the heading "TRUSTED BY TEAMS AT" followed by a list of logos of companies.
  *   Enterprise Section: Contains the heading "Enterprise-Ready" followed by a description of apps running on Fly Machines and call-to-action buttons "Enterprise Features" and "Fly.io Security".
  *   Footer Call-to-Action: Contains the heading "Build Whatever You Can Think Up (and Give Your Users The Same Power)", a description of the Fly.io platform, and a call-to-action button "Spin up a Sandbox".
  *   Footer: Contains sections for "Company", "Articles", "Resources", "Contact", and "Legal" with lists of links under each. It also contains copyright information.

3. Interactive Elements:
  *   Header: Links to Products, Docs, Customers, Pricing, Articles, Community, and Status. Buttons to Sign In and Get Started.
  *   Hero Section: Button labeled "Deploy your app".
  *   Feature Section 2: Button labeled "Check 'em out!".
  *   Tech Section: A "Learn More" link, and a "Next" button.
  *   Agents Section: Button labeled "Build for scale from Day One".
  *   Enterprise Section: Buttons labeled "Enterprise Features" and "Fly.io Security".
  *   Footer Call-to-Action: Button labeled "Spin up a Sandbox".
  *   Footer: Lists of links under "Company", "Articles", "Resources", "Contact", and "Legal".

4. Content Details:
  *   Headline: "Build fast. Run any code fearlessly."
  *   Description: "The platform for devs who just want to ship. Powered by sandboxes that let you deploy any code with confidence."
  *   Feature 1 Heading: "Modern Compute Without the Complexity"
  *   Feature 1 Description: "For builders who need compute that keeps up with their ideas. Fly Machines are hardware-virtualized containers that launch instantly and run only when you need them. Deploy an app in minutes or run untrusted code in isolated sandboxes."
  *   Feature 2 Heading: "Sandboxes That Feel Like a Superpower"
  *   Feature 2 Description: "Spin up hardware-isolated sandboxes for running AI-generated code in complete safety. Every Sprite is a self-contained environment, ready for action in under a second. Checkpoint your entire environment, run anything, and restore if you break something. Pay only for actual CPU and memory consumption, down to the second."
  *   Feature 3 Heading: "Storage That Keeps Up"
  *   Feature 3 Description: "Fast local NVMe for low-latency work, plus global, durable object storage for data that needs to stick around. Snapshot environments, persist state, and scale storage right alongside your sandboxes."
  *   Feature 4 Heading: "Built-In Private Networking"
  *   Feature 4 Description: "Private networks per sandbox, granular routing, and end-to-end encryption - all automatic."
  *   Feature 5 List: "VMs That Do Everything You Need", "Fork Off VMs Like They're Processes", "Built for Distributed Systems", "Get Right in Your Users' Faces"
  *   Tech Section Heading: "Use the Tech You Love"
  *   Tech Section Description: "Build with your favorite framework. No Dockerfile? No problem: our CLI generates containers for most popular frameworks, including Rails, Phoenix, Django, Node, Laravel, and .NET."
  *   Agents Section Heading: "Agents Run Better on Sprites"
  *   Agents Section Description: "You don't have to be a cloud guru to build scalable agents. Run every instance on its own VM with dedicated CPU memory, networking, and a private filesystem. Forget wrestling with shared runtimes or noisy neighbors. Get persistent brains for ephemeral workers when you don't."
  *   Enterprise Section Heading: "Enterprise-Ready"
  *   Enterprise Section Description: "Apps running on Fly Machines are KVM hardware-isolated, built on a memory-safe stack and running directly on our own metal."
  *   Footer Call-to-Action Headline: "Build Whatever You Can Think Up (and Give Your Users The Same Power)"
  *   Footer Call-to-Action Description: "Fly.io is the platform that gets out of your way, running on the infrastructure that lets you run any code without fear. See how fast you can get started."
  *   List of features: Single Sign-On, Guaranteed Support Response Times, SOC2 Type 2 Attested, Memory-safe Rust and Go stack, CI/CD Integration.

1. Page Overview: Pricing page for Fly.io, highlighting the flexible billing options and features.

2. Sections:
    *   Header: Contains links to Products, Docs, Customers, Pricing, Articles, Community, Status, Sign In and a button labeled "Get Started."
    *   Hero Section: Contains the title "Public Cloud Billing The Easy Way", explanatory text about the usage-based billing model, and a call-to-action button "Launch Now".
    *   Billing Options: A section highlighting three billing options: "Pay-as-You-Go Infrastructure" with a short description and a "Learn More" link, "Serious Support" with a price and a "Learn More" link, and "Pay up Front and Save" with a discount offer and a "Learn More" link.
    *   Calculator Feature: Area describing the pricing calculator feature with the heading "Everyone Loves a Calculator", supporting text, and a button to "Calculate Your Cost".
    *   Enterprise Option: Area with the title "Enterprise-Ready", a description of enterprise support and SLA options, and a "Contact Sales" link.
    *   Compliance Feature: Section describing the compliance features, the heading "Compliance Made Easy", the description of available HIPPA options, and a "Get Started" link.
    *   Accidental Deployment Policy: Area outlining the policy for accidental deployments, with the heading "Accidental Deployments Are on the House" and a description of the refund policy.
    *   Features List: A section with the title "Features That Just Make Sense," a short description, a "Start Now" button, and a list of features with checkmarks. The feature list includes: FlyCTL CLI: Orchestration from your terminal, Unlimited users per organization, Unlimited organizations, Aggregated billing across organizations, Private networking, SSO authentication, and ACLs and Narrowly scoped tokens.
    *   Trusted By Section: Includes the title "TRUSTED BY TEAMS AT" and a list of company logos.
    *   Footer: Contains links to Company (About, Pricing, Jobs), Articles (Blog, Phoenix Files, Laravel Bytes, Ruby Dispatch, Django Beats, JavaScript Journal), Resources (Docs, Customers, Support, Support Metrics, Status), Contact (GitHub, Twitter, Community), and Legal (Security, Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, Acceptable Use Policy). Also includes a copyright notice.

3. Interactive Elements:
    *   "Launch Now" button: Navigates to the product.
    *   "Learn More" links (3): Navigates to more information about each billing option.
    *   "Calculate Your Cost" button: Navigates to the pricing calculator.
    *   "Contact Sales" link: Navigates to a contact form or sales page.
    *   "Get Started" link: Navigates to a registration or signup page.
    *   "Start Now" button: Navigates to a signup or trial page.
    *   Links in the header (Products, Docs, Customers, Pricing, Articles, Community, Status): Navigates to respective pages.
    *   "Sign In" link: Navigates to the sign-in page.
    *   "Get Started" button in the header: Navigates to a registration or signup page.
    *   Links in the footer: Navigates to respective pages (About, Pricing, Jobs, Blog, Phoenix Files, Laravel Bytes, Ruby Dispatch, Django Beats, JavaScript Journal, Docs, Customers, Support, Support Metrics, Status, GitHub, Twitter, Community, Security, Privacy Policy, Terms of Service, Acceptable Use Policy).

4. Content Details:
    *   Page Title: Public Cloud Billing The Easy Way
    *   Hero Section Text: Plans get complicated, so we just charge based on usage. Pick and choose which pieces you need for your application; that's all you'll see on your invoice.
    *   Pay-as-You-Go Infrastructure: Micro VMs, persistent storage, and GPUs, oh my!
    *   Serious Support: Access to our dedicated team of engineers. Starting at $29/month.
    *   Pay up Front and Save: Get 40% off by making a machine reservation.
    *   Everyone Loves a Calculator: Want to know how much Flyjo will cost for your application? Try our new pricing calculator. Enter your expected usage and we'll give you a personalized estimate.
    *   Enterprise-Ready: Need to run larger workloads with custom resource configurations, SLA requirements, or emergency support? We've got you covered.
    *   Compliance Made Easy: Everything you need for HIPAA-compliant workloads, from BAAs to SOC2s, for just $99/month.
    *   Accidental Deployments Are on the House: Maybe your CI/CD system screwed up and left a whole staging environment deployed. Or maybe you typed an extra zero on a scale command. Whatever it was: if you didn't expect it, and it looks weird on your bill, tell us. We'll waive or refund any unintended charges for paid support customers.
    *   Features That Just Make Sense: Want to feel special? Check Under Your Seat! All Fly.io users take home these wonderful prizes (and more).
    *   List of Features: FlyCTL CLI: Orchestration from your terminal, Unlimited users per organization, Unlimited organizations, Aggregated billing across organizations, Private networking, SSO authentication, ACLs and Narrowly scoped tokens.
    *   "TRUSTED BY TEAMS AT": Section with logos of companies that use Fly.io

1. Page Overview:
Landing page for a browser infrastructure service. The primary goal is to introduce the service and encourage users to get started.

2. Sections:
   - Header Section: Includes company logo and navigation links.
     - Content: Company logo (Kernel), navigation links labeled "Customers", "Pricing", "Docs", "Blog", "Sign In", "Sign Up", and "Book a Demo".  Also displays a banner with text "Kernel announces its partnership with Vercel Marketplace" which links to "Learn More".
   - Hero Section: Presents the core value proposition of the service.
     - Content: Headline "Crazy Fast Browser Infrastructure", descriptive text including: "Launch browsers in 325ms or less • Anti-bot detection • Session reuse • Live view & replays • Autoscaling • Authentication", and a call-to-action button.
   - Logos Section: Displays logos of companies.
     - Content: Includes logos with labels: "Range Slice", "Concourse", "Cash App", "Woflow", "Rye", and "CLAR".
   - Description Section: Provides a more detailed explanation of the service.
     - Content: Text describing Kernel as providing a browser for web agents to access the Internet in the cloud and highlighting the ease of launching and scaling web agents and browser automations. Includes a stylized image.

3. Interactive Elements:
   - "Get Started" button: This button serves as a call-to-action to encourage users to begin using the service.
   - Navigation links in the header: These provide access to different sections of the website or external resources such as documentation and the blog.
   - Vercel Partnership banner which links to "Learn More".

4. Content Details:
   - Headline: "Crazy Fast Browser Infrastructure"
   - Supporting Text: "Launch browsers in 325ms or less • Anti-bot detection • Session reuse • Live view & replays • Autoscaling • Authentication"
   - Call-to-action: "Get Started"
   - Company Description: "Kernel gives your web agent a browser to access the Internet in the cloud. Our browsers-as-a-service platform makes it easy to launch and scale web agents and browser automations."
   - Navigation links: "Customers", "Pricing", "Docs", "Blog", "Sign In", "Sign Up", "Book a Demo"
   - Announcement: "Kernel announces its partnership with Vercel Marketplace" with a link to "Learn More".
